## Technical Overview

### Architecture
This project is an MVC-style analytics platform built with PHP and MySQL on Apache.
Data is collected via a custom `collector.js` script served from `collector.sanisilva.site`,
which tracks static, performance, and activity data from `test.sanisilva.site`.
The data is stored in a MySQL database (`collector_db`) and visualized on the reporting backend.

### Stack
- **Frontend:** Bootstrap 5, Chart.js
- **Backend:** PHP 8.3, Apache with mod_rewrite
- **Database:** MySQL 8.0
- **Data Collection:** Vanilla JS (collector.js)

### Features
- Session-based authentication with 3 user roles (superadmin, analyst, viewer)
- 3 report categories: Static, Performance, Activity
- Charts using Chart.js (bar, doughnut, line)
- Data tables with live MySQL data
- Analyst comments per report
- PDF export via print-friendly URL (?print=1)
- User management (superadmin only)
- 403/404 error pages

